<subSubSection id="E98E6553FFEFFFFD388AFA53AE0E9BC6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="description">
<paragraph id="A12B36D8FFEFFFFD388AFA53AA689B66" blockId="4.[151,1436,1498,1924]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis id="93E0EACAFFEFFFFD388AFA53AE1A98D6" bold="true" box="[151,303,1498,1524]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Description.</emphasis>
Body length: ɗ, 
<quantity id="666C9B3DFFEFFFFD39EAFA53AD7898D6" box="[503,589,1498,1524]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5mm</quantity>
. Body colour generally dark brown; vertex with blackish brown apically (
<figureCitation id="39AF2A5DFFEFFFFD3882F98BAFD19B3E" box="[159,228,1538,1564]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1718,1742]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,311,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[167,1413,277,1692]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrta hirsuta A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; D, male genital capsule, lateral view; E, style and connective, dorsal view; F, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; G, valve and style, ventral view; H, base of aedeagus and dorsal connective, anteroventral view; I, male genital capsule, dorsal view; J, aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182577/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number id="175C24FFFFEFFFFD38C4F98BAFD19B3E" box="[217,228,1538,1564]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A); face pale yellow, anteclypeus with pair of stout brown setae apically (
<figureCitation id="39AF2A5DFFEFFFFD3C7DF98BAB909B3E" box="[1120,1189,1538,1564]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1718,1742]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,311,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[167,1413,277,1692]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrta hirsuta A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; D, male genital capsule, lateral view; E, style and connective, dorsal view; F, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; G, valve and style, ventral view; H, base of aedeagus and dorsal connective, anteroventral view; I, male genital capsule, dorsal view; J, aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182577/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number id="175C24FFFFEFFFFD3C84F98BAB909B3E" box="[1177,1189,1538,1564]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Head and thorax with somewhat dense pale short setae. Scutellum with some short tufts of black setae laterally (
<figureCitation id="39AF2A5DFFEFFFFD3CEFF9A3AA019B66" box="[1266,1332,1578,1604]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1718,1742]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,311,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[167,1413,277,1692]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrta hirsuta A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; D, male genital capsule, lateral view; E, style and connective, dorsal view; F, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; G, valve and style, ventral view; H, base of aedeagus and dorsal connective, anteroventral view; I, male genital capsule, dorsal view; J, aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182577/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number id="175C24FFFFEFFFFD3D34F9A3AA019B66" box="[1321,1332,1578,1604]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A12B36D8FFEFFFFD38D8F9DBAE0E9BC6" blockId="4.[151,1436,1498,1924]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Male pygofer with distal margin broadly rounded in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="39AF2A5DFFEFFFFD3BE6F9DBAB779B4E" box="[1019,1090,1618,1644]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1718,1742]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,311,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[167,1413,277,1692]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrta hirsuta A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; D, male genital capsule, lateral view; E, style and connective, dorsal view; F, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; G, valve and style, ventral view; H, base of aedeagus and dorsal connective, anteroventral view; I, male genital capsule, dorsal view; J, aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182577/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number id="175C24FFFFEFFFFD3C2AF9DBAB779B4E" box="[1079,1090,1618,1644]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
D); subgenital plate slightly extending beyond apex of pygofer side, apex acute in ventral view (
<figureCitation id="39AF2A5DFFEFFFFD3BDFF9F3AB3F9BB6" box="[962,1034,1658,1684]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1718,1742]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,311,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[167,1413,277,1692]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrta hirsuta A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; D, male genital capsule, lateral view; E, style and connective, dorsal view; F, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; G, valve and style, ventral view; H, base of aedeagus and dorsal connective, anteroventral view; I, male genital capsule, dorsal view; J, aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182577/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Figs 
<number id="175C24FFFFEFFFFD3BE2F9F3AB3F9BB6" box="[1023,1034,1658,1684]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
D, G). Aedeagal shaft with dense tubercles laterally, apex strongly narrowed distally in ventral view (
<figureCitation id="39AF2A5DFFEFFFFD3BA3F92BAB339B9E" box="[958,1030,1698,1724]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1718,1742]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,311,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[167,1413,277,1692]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrta hirsuta A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; D, male genital capsule, lateral view; E, style and connective, dorsal view; F, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; G, valve and style, ventral view; H, base of aedeagus and dorsal connective, anteroventral view; I, male genital capsule, dorsal view; J, aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182577/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Figs 
<number id="175C24FFFFEFFFFD3BE6F92BAB339B9E" box="[1019,1030,1698,1724]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C, F, L). Xth segment moderately long (
<figureCitation id="39AF2A5DFFEFFFFD38C6F943AE2B9BC6" box="[219,286,1738,1764]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1718,1742]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,311,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[167,1413,277,1692]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrta hirsuta A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; D, male genital capsule, lateral view; E, style and connective, dorsal view; F, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; G, valve and style, ventral view; H, base of aedeagus and dorsal connective, anteroventral view; I, male genital capsule, dorsal view; J, aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182577/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<date id="D52A1018FFEFFFFD390FF943AE2B9BC6" box="[274,286,1738,1764]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<number id="175C24FFFFEFFFFD390FF943AE2B9BC6" box="[274,286,1738,1764]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.0">1</number>
</date>
</figureCitation>
I).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
